Proposed change to address this issue:

{code}
git show 193e4e1a849e592f27ef7b7e705259bfa43c5fa3
{code}

This change clears the orphan count for an address on allocation which prevents the count from one allocation being used on subsequent allocations if an instance does not move to the running state (e.g. if volume creation times out)
